theorem P1_of_P1_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 (closure (A : Set X)) → Topology.P1 A := by
  intro hP1Cl
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1Cl ⊢
  intro x hxA
  -- Step 1: view `x` as a point of `closure A`.
  have hxCl : x ∈ closure A := subset_closure hxA
  -- Step 2: apply `P1` for `closure A`.
  have hxTarget : x ∈ closure (interior (closure A)) := hP1Cl hxCl
  -- Step 3: transfer membership via monotonicity.
  have hsubset : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
    closure_interior_subset_closure_interior_closure (A := A)
  exact hsubset hxTarget

theorem closure_interior_closure_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
  -- The interior of `closure A` is contained in `closure A`.
  have h₁ : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  have h₂ : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure (closure A) :=
    closure_mono h₁
  -- Simplify `closure (closure A)` to `closure A`.
  simpa [closure_closure] using h₂
